Xenon UI Library Documentation
============================

Initialization
-------------
First, load the Xenon UI library:
```lua
local library = loadstring(game:HttpGet('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/arabdogwater/xenonuilib/refs/heads/main/library'))()
```

Then create a new window:
```lua
local Window = library:Create("Your UI Name", "Subtitle")  -- Note the colon (:) instead of dot (.)
```

Creating Tabs
------------
To create a new tab:
local tab = Window:Tab("Tab Name", imageId) -- imageId is optional

Available UI Elements
-------------------

1. Button
---------
Parameters:
- text: string (button text)
- info: string (info text shown when clicking down arrow)
- callback: function (executed when button is clicked)

Example:
local button = tab:Button("Click Me", "This is info text", function()
    print("Button clicked!")
end)

2. Toggle
---------
Parameters:
- text: string (toggle text)
- info: string (info text shown when clicking down arrow)
- state: boolean (initial state)
- callback: function (executed when toggle state changes)
- dont_run_on_start: boolean (optional, prevents callback from running on creation)

Example:
local toggle = tab:Toggle("Enable Feature", "Toggle info", false, function(state)
    print("Toggle state:", state)
end)

3. Slider
---------
Parameters:
- name: string (slider name)
- min: number (minimum value)
- max: number (maximum value)
- starting: number (initial value)
- callback: function (executed when value changes)

Example:
local slider = tab:Slider("Speed", 1, 100, 50, function(value)
    print("Speed set to:", value)
end)

4. Dropdown
----------
Parameters:
- name: string (dropdown name)
- list: table (array of options)
- callback: function (executed when selection changes)

Example:
local dropdown = tab:Dropdown("Select Option", {"Option 1", "Option 2", "Option 3"}, function(selected)
    print("Selected:", selected)
end)

5. Label
--------
Parameters:
- text: string (label text)

Example:
local label = tab:Label("This is a label")

6. TextBox
---------
Parameters:
- text: string (textbox placeholder)
- callback: function (executed when text is entered)

Example:
local textbox = tab:TextBox("Enter text", function(text)
    print("Entered text:", text)
end)

7. Keybind
---------
Parameters:
- name: string (keybind name)
- key: Enum.KeyCode (default key)
- blacklist: table (array of keys to blacklist)
- callback: function (executed when key is pressed)

Example:
local keybind = tab:Keybind("Press Key", Enum.KeyCode.E, {"W", "A", "S", "D"}, function(key)
    print("Key pressed:", key)
end)

8. Separator
-----------
Creates a visual separator line between elements.

Example:
local separator = tab:Separator()

Additional Features
-----------------

1. Notifications
---------------
To show a notification:
Window:Notification("Your notification text")

2. UI Toggle
-----------
To toggle the entire UI visibility:
Window:ToggleUI()

3. Dragging
----------
The UI window can be dragged by clicking and holding the top bar.

4. Ripple Effect
---------------
All clickable elements have a ripple effect animation when clicked.

5. Info System
-------------
Most elements have an info system that can be accessed by clicking the down arrow icon.

Complete Example
--------------
Here's a complete example showing how to use the library:

```lua
-- Load the library
local library = loadstring(game:HttpGet('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/arabdogwater/xenonuilib/refs/heads/main/library'))()

-- Create the main window
local Window = library:Create("My Script", "v1.0")

-- Create a tab
local MainTab = Window:Tab("Main", 1234567) -- 1234567 is an example image ID

-- Add some elements
MainTab:Label("Welcome to my script!")

MainTab:Button("Click Me", "This button does something", function()
    print("Button clicked!")
end)

MainTab:Toggle("Enable Feature", "Toggles a feature", false, function(state)
    print("Feature state:", state)
end)

MainTab:Slider("Speed", 1, 100, 50, function(value)
    print("Speed set to:", value)
end)

MainTab:Dropdown("Select Option", {"Option 1", "Option 2", "Option 3"}, function(selected)
    print("Selected:", selected)
end)

MainTab:Separator()

MainTab:TextBox("Enter text", function(text)
    print("Entered text:", text)
end)

MainTab:Keybind("Press Key", Enum.KeyCode.E, {"W", "A", "S", "D"}, function(key)
    print("Key pressed:", key)
end)

-- Show a notification
Window:Notification("Script loaded successfully!")
```

Notes
-----
- All elements have Show() and Hide() methods to control visibility
- The UI is draggable and can be moved around the screen
- Elements are automatically positioned in the order they are created
- The library handles all animations and transitions automatically
- All callbacks are executed in a protected environment to prevent errors
- The UI uses a modern design with smooth animations and transitions
- The library is optimized for performance and minimal impact on game performance 
